I am a Special Counsel in the Banking and Finance team of King & Wood Mallesons, based in Sydney. 

My focus in any commercial dispute is to at all times remain highly responsive to, and focussed on, my client's commercial objectives and to achieve those objectives as time and cost effectively as possible.

Over the last decade I have developed a particular expertise with regards insolvency related matters and have provided advice to clients in relation to the full range of issues arising in a distressed environment including security enforcement, corporate restructuring, insolvency 鈥榩roofing鈥� strategies, security ranking (including PPSA issues), and voidable transaction and insolvency trading claims.  

Key matters I have been involved with during my career include Arrium  (acting for the financiers), Paladin (acting for the administrators), McAleese (acting for the administrators), Angas (acting for the trustee). Forge  (acting for the liquidators), Opes Prime (advising a key lender), Centro (advising various lenders), ION (acting for the receivers), and Sons of Gwalia (acting for the administrators), together with a host of SME based instructions. 

